I did, however, find the old Dutch hospital (now an alluring arcade of caf√©s) and the Wolvendaal Church (1749), with its little pews for slaves. Best of all was the lovely, rambling Galle Face Hotel, where – beyond the lobby – the ambient sound changes from congestion to surf. It’s the only hotel I’ve ever stayed in with a professional scarecrow, who prowls around armed with a catapult.
